---
import SiteLayout from "@/layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="About | todo-app"
  description="About the Astro migration and the local-first todo app."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">About</h1>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-stone-600">
      todo-app is a local-first task manager. Tasks, projects, and preferences stay in the browser,
      and the existing Solid application continues to handle the interactive experience.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-stone-600">
      This PR moves the site to Astro so the project can support simple content pages alongside the
      app without rewriting the app itself.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
